        <h1 id="person">Validation</h1>
        <a href="#body" class="top" title="Back up to the top of the page" >Top</a>
      </div>
      <div class="body">
        <p>
           Validation of a resource description ensures that it complies to an instance
           of the SPASE data model. While the SPASE data model is relatively stable, there
           are new versions released from time-to-time. Each version has a prescribed set of
           elements for each resource class.
         </p>
         <p>
         	In addition to conforming to a specific version of SPASE data model, many a resource 
         	descriptions contain references to other resources through resource identifiers and to
         	stored resources using a URL. A full validation ensures the integrity of these references.
         </p>
         <p>
         	SPASE provides both an <a target="_blank" href="http://spase-group.org/tools/validate">on-line</a>
         validation tool and a command-line validation tool as part of 
         the <a target="_blank" href="http://spase-group.org/tools/resource/">SPASE Resource Tools</a>.
     </div> <!-- End of Body -->
   </div> <!-- End of Section -->

